# ============================================
# Job Application Agent - Cursor Rules
# ============================================

## Project Purpose
This is an AI-powered Job Application Automation Agent.
It scrapes jobs from 7 platforms (Naukri, Internshala, LinkedIn,
Indeed, Glassdoor, Wellfound, RemoteOK), ranks them using Groq LLM,
tailors resumes per job, generates cover letters, analyzes skill gaps,
and sends Telegram notifications.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.10+
- Groq API (llama-3.3-70b-versatile) - Free LLM
- Playwright - Browser automation & scraping
- Flask - Web interface (optional)
- Schedule - Auto daily runs
- Google Sheets API - Application tracking
- Telegram Bot API - Phone notifications

## Folder Structure
- main.py              → Entry point (run this)
- scheduler.py         → Auto daily scheduler
- agent/               → Core orchestrator
- scrapers/            → One file per platform
- utils/               → Shared utilities
- config/              → Resume + credentials (gitignored)
- output/              → Generated files (gitignored)
- logs/                → Run logs (gitignored)

## Platforms Supported
Indian: naukri, internshala
Global: linkedin, indeed, glassdoor, wellfound, remoteok

## Coding Guidelines
- Always use environment variables for secrets
- All scrapers return list of dicts with:
  title, company, location, skills, description, url, platform
- All Groq calls must have try/except with fallback
- Use setup_logger() from utils/logger.py everywhere
- All scrapers must have _get_sample_jobs() fallback

## Adding a New Scraper
1. Create scrapers/newsite_scraper.py
2. Follow NaukriScraper pattern
3. Add to agent/job_agent.py scrapers dict
4. Add platform name to .env PLATFORMS list

## Run Commands
# Normal run
python main.py

# Scheduled daily run at 8am
python scheduler.py

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
playwright install chromium

## Environment Setup
cp .env.example .env
# Fill in GROQ_API_KEY (free at console.groq.com)
# Fill in TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN + TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID (optional)
# Edit config/resume.txt with your resume

## Performance Scoring (1-10,000)
Score = Jobs_Found(2000) + Ranking(3000) + Tailoring(3000) + Speed(1000) + Platforms(1000)
Current benchmark: 8000/10,000

## Security
- Never commit .env
- Never commit config/google_creds.json
- Never commit config/resume.txt
- All secrets via environment variables only